Vice President Mike Pence, Dr. Deborah Birx, and Seema Verma met with long-term, post-acute, and palliative care providers to discuss the impact of the Coronavirus on the industry. The Vice President emphasized the administration's commitment to the safety and health of the American people. Administrator Verma announced new guidelines for surveyors when surveying facilities with confirmed or presumptive cases of the virus. Ambassador Birx stressed the importance of focusing on populations at higher risk. The safety and quality of nursing homes and long-term care facilities remain a priority for the administration. The participants in the meeting included various healthcare leaders and organizations. For more information on the Coronavirus, visit the CDC's website.